{"id":"mai-ob9f","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"mai ticket vs mai create — two ways to create, unclear difference","priority":2,"tags":["ux","cli"],"body":"\"mai ticket\" is the documented shortcut (sets kind=ticket, type from -t flag).\\n\"mai create\" is the raw creator (kind from -k, type from -t).\\n\\nBut they share the same -t flag with DIFFERENT meanings:\\n- mai ticket -t task = sets type to \"task\" (correct, -t means --type here)\\n- mai create -t \"My Title\" = sets TYPE to \"My Title\" (wrong — user expected title)\\n\\nThe aliasing is confusing. Either:\\n1. mai ticket is the only way to create (mai create removed), OR\\n2. mai create uses --title/-T for title, --type for type, OR\\n3. Document the difference prominently in --help (which doesn't exist, see mai-01dl)","timestamp":"2026-03-28T22:39:43Z","branch":"main"}
